ploads/2021/06/02053851/transition-spire-170mm-travel-29er-enduro-bike-purple-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02053851/transition-spire-170mm-travel-29er-enduro-bike-purple-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02053851/transition-spire-170mm-travel-29er-enduro-bike-purple-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02053851/transition-spire-170mm-travel-29er-enduro-bike-purple-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Building off the Sentinel is the all-new Transition Spire, their longest travel 29″ trail bike. Just like the new mixed wheel size Transition Patrol, the Spire geometry is subtly adjustable via use of a flip chip which dictates the position of the lower shock mount.&nbsp;</p><figure id=\"attachment_260758\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260758\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle.jpg\" alt=\"transition spire\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-200x300.jpg 200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-800x1200.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-80x120.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-768x1152.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-1024x1536.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-696x1044.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-1068x1602.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-280x420.jpg 280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-200x300.jpg 200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-800x1200.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-80x120.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-768x1152.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-1024x1536.jpg 1024w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-696x1044.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-1068x1602.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104510/transition-spire-head-angle-280x420.jpg 280w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260758\">The Transition Spire runs a 170mm travel 44mm offset fork</figcaption></figure><p>In its lowest, slackest configuration, the Spire has the slackest head angle out of all Transition mountain bikes at 62.5°. That’s half a degree slacker than the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2019/07/31/transition-cranks-it-to-11-again-with-updated-tr11-carbon-dh-bike/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">TR11</a> downhill bike. That’s paired with a marvelously steep effective seat tube angle of 77.6° in size large.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-medrectangle-3\"></span></p><figure id=\"attachment_260753\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260753\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1.jpg\" alt=\"transition spire 170mm travel enduro bike\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-630x420.jpg 630w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02104105/transition-spire-frame-details-1-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260753\">All frames are compatible with 27.5 rear wheels in the high geo adjust position</figcaption></figure><p>Transition adjust that angle depending on frame size; it’s at its steepest on the small frame at 79.6° and its slackest on the XXL at 77.2°. That geometry will put the rider’s hips in a commanding position above the bottom bracket resulting in what should be a very pedal-able long travel bike.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting.jpg\" alt=\"transition spire geometry low setting\" width=\"1200\" height=\"779\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-297x193.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-800x519.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-120x78.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-768x499.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-696x452.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-1068x693.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-647x420.jpg 647w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb13 src ng ngcb13 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-297x193.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-800x519.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-120x78.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-768x499.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-696x452.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-1068x693.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095701/transition-spire-geometry-low-setting-647x420.jpg 647w\"></a></p><p>Switching the flip chip to the high setting steepens the head angle to 63°, while also steepening the effective seat tube angle by 0.5° across the board. It also raises the height of the bottom bracket by 7mm to 350mm.</p><p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumo