y-high-setting.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095655/transition-spire-geometry-high-setting.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095655/transition-spire-geometry-high-setting-297x220.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095655/transition-spire-geometry-high-setting-800x593.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095655/transition-spire-geometry-high-setting-120x89.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095655/transition-spire-geometry-high-setting-768x569.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095655/transition-spire-geometry-high-setting-485x360.jpg 485w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095655/transition-spire-geometry-high-setting-696x516.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095655/transition-spire-geometry-high-setting-1068x791.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095655/transition-spire-geometry-high-setting-567x420.jpg 567w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02095655/transition-spire-geometry-high-setting-80x60.jpg 80w\"></p><p>With 165mm cranks (on every frame size), that should ensure decent ground clearance from pedal strikes. Though, it will of course depend on the amount of sag you run the rear shock at. Which brings me to…</p><h3>Spire Leverage Curves</h3><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111029/transition-spire-23-percent-overall-progression-le