hainstays.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02101833/transition-spire-leverage-ration-graph-long-short-chainstays.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02101833/transition-spire-leverage-ration-graph-long-short-chainstays-297x173.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02101833/transition-spire-leverage-ration-graph-long-short-chainstays-800x467.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02101833/transition-spire-leverage-ration-graph-long-short-chainstays-120x70.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02101833/transition-spire-leverage-ration-graph-long-short-chainstays-768x448.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02101833/transition-spire-leverage-ration-graph-long-short-chainstays-696x406.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02101833/transition-spire-leverage-ration-graph-long-short-chainstays-1068x623.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02101833/transition-spire-leverage-ration-graph-long-short-chainstays-720x420.jpg 720w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-260749\">Transition publish two leverage curves for the Spire, reflective of the two chainstay lengths</figcaption></figure><p>Its 170mm rear wheel travel is delivered, as ever, by Transition’s “Party Time” leverage curves, with a 23% overall progression said to provide enough bottom out control for use with both air and coil shocks, with a recommended sag range of 27-33%. Transition say that will allow the rider to tune the feel of the bike “from a firm and snappy jump and slash mode, to a more supple and active full on party mode”. That not progressive enough for you? Fear not, it’s likely <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/02/24/cascade-components-links-for-sentinel-and-heckler-emtb-increase-travel-progression/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Cascade Components</a> are working on a more progressive aftermarket link for the Spire as you’re reading this.</p><h4>Frame Details</h4><figure id=\"attachment_260763\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-260763\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111516/transition-spire-oramge.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111516/transition-spire-oramge.jpg\" alt=\"transition spire orange\" width=\"1200\" height=\"744\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111516/transition-spire-oramge.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111516/transition-spire-oramge-297x184.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111516/transition-spire-oramge-800x496.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111516/transition-spire-oramge-120x74.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111516/transition-spire-oramge-768x476.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111516/transition-spire-oramge-696x432.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111516/transition-spire-oramge-1068x662.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/02111516/transition-spire-oramge-677x420.jpg 677w,https:/